subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Fig. 11
) general characters: genitalia narrow (l/w ratio ca. 47/8); paramere tips elongate, slightly widened, distal ends pointed, lateral margins straight from plsa to distal tip, medial margins of tips emarginate, distal end of tips extending slightly beyond aedeagus, in lateral view tips narrow, sharply pointed; aedeagus lanceolate in dorsal/ventral views, widest at ca. midlength, tapering to sharp distal end, with narrowly sclerotized lateral margins; basal piece slightly shorter than parameres (ratio ca. 23/25), tapering from distal end to slightly asymmetrical orifice, rim of orifice sclerotized.
